WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:03.760 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:03.760 --> 00:00:05.640 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.640 --> 00:00:10.350 align:middle line:84%
>> "Thinking Allowed,"
conversations on the leading

00:00:10.350 --> 00:00:14.280 align:middle line:84%
edge of knowledge and discovery,
with psychologist Jeffrey

00:00:14.280 --> 00:00:15.080 align:middle line:90%
Mishlove.

00:00:15.080 --> 00:00:31.670 align:middle line:90%


00:00:31.670 --> 00:00:32.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello, and welcome.

00:00:32.610 --> 00:00:34.160 align:middle line:90%
I'm Jeffrey Mishlove.

00:00:34.160 --> 00:00:37.010 align:middle line:84%
Our topic today
is how to know God

00:00:37.010 --> 00:00:39.410 align:middle line:90%
without the necessity of belief.

00:00:39.410 --> 00:00:42.770 align:middle line:84%
I've been talking with
physicist Russell Targ, author

00:00:42.770 --> 00:00:46.880 align:middle line:84%
of five books, each of which has
the word "mind" in the title,

00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:52.500 align:middle line:84%
"Mind Reach," "The Heart of
the Mind," "Miracles of Mind,"

00:00:52.500 --> 00:00:55.340 align:middle line:90%
"The Mind Race," and others.

00:00:55.340 --> 00:00:56.140 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Russell.

00:00:56.140 --> 00:00:56.941 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello.

00:00:56.941 --> 00:00:58.240 align:middle line:90%
I'm happy to be with you.

00:00:58.240 --> 00:01:01.710 align:middle line:84%
>> In the first part of
this two-part series,

00:01:01.710 --> 00:01:07.210 align:middle line:84%
we talked about the principle
of nonlocality in science,

00:01:07.210 --> 00:01:10.700 align:middle line:84%
a fundamental principle
which I think is a key

00:01:10.700 --> 00:01:14.990 align:middle line:84%
because we're in an era now
where science and spirituality

00:01:14.990 --> 00:01:16.670 align:middle line:90%
are finding common ground.

00:01:16.670 --> 00:01:19.790 align:middle line:84%
For centuries, it
seemed as if science

00:01:19.790 --> 00:01:23.300 align:middle line:84%
struggled to distinguish
itself from the dogma

00:01:23.300 --> 00:01:24.680 align:middle line:90%
of religious traditions.

00:01:24.680 --> 00:01:28.760 align:middle line:84%
Now, things seem to be
moving back the other way.

00:01:28.760 --> 00:01:31.850 align:middle line:84%
>> I think a lot of progress is
made because what we understand

00:01:31.850 --> 00:01:35.540 align:middle line:84%
is the experience of God
as a testable hypothesis.

00:01:35.540 --> 00:01:38.780 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to give up
your discerning mind in order

00:01:38.780 --> 00:01:43.400 align:middle line:84%
to participate in the experience
of love, the experience of God,

00:01:43.400 --> 00:01:45.000 align:middle line:90%
that's available.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:48.320 align:middle line:84%
For example, in the Buddhist
tradition, or many meditative

00:01:48.320 --> 00:01:52.040 align:middle line:84%
traditions, they say if
you will quiet your mind

00:01:52.040 --> 00:01:54.890 align:middle line:84%
and surrender to the
experience of God

00:01:54.890 --> 00:01:58.100 align:middle line:84%
or surrender to the
experience of love,

00:01:58.100 --> 00:02:01.700 align:middle line:84%
then you are likely to have
a certain kind of loving

00:02:01.700 --> 00:02:02.690 align:middle line:90%
experience.

00:02:02.690 --> 00:02:07.650 align:middle line:84%
You'll reside in this loving
syrup that we've talked about.

00:02:07.650 --> 00:02:11.400 align:middle line:84%
And the teaching then is, after
you have done this practice,

00:02:11.400 --> 00:02:13.790 align:middle line:84%
come back, write
me a lab report,

00:02:13.790 --> 00:02:15.500 align:middle line:84%
and let me know what
you experienced--

00:02:15.500 --> 00:02:20.990 align:middle line:84%
does not require you to believe
in any panoply of superstition,

00:02:20.990 --> 00:02:23.080 align:middle line:90%
or deities, or anything else.

00:02:23.080 --> 00:02:26.930 align:middle line:84%
It's that you have this unit of
experience, this one with God

00:02:26.930 --> 00:02:30.590 align:middle line:84%
experience that's
available without having

00:02:30.590 --> 00:02:33.110 align:middle line:84%
to give up your
life as a scientist

00:02:33.110 --> 00:02:34.110 align:middle line:90%
or a thoughtful person.

00:02:34.110 --> 00:02:36.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, I think we ought
to point out that what

00:02:36.800 --> 00:02:40.070 align:middle line:84%
we're talking about here is very
different from the sophomore

00:02:40.070 --> 00:02:43.820 align:middle line:84%
philosophy class in which
we explore, does God exist?

00:02:43.820 --> 00:02:48.290 align:middle line:84%
Because from that
perspective, God

00:02:48.290 --> 00:02:50.150 align:middle line:90%
is not a testable hypothesis.

00:02:50.150 --> 00:02:53.090 align:middle line:84%
And, in fact, the Buddhists
would say the same, too.

00:02:53.090 --> 00:02:54.710 align:middle line:90%
They would say God is--

00:02:54.710 --> 00:02:57.860 align:middle line:90%
there is no selfness to God.

00:02:57.860 --> 00:03:01.160 align:middle line:84%
>> The question of the existence
of God never gets anywhere.

00:03:01.160 --> 00:03:04.400 align:middle line:84%
The contribution of
the logical positivists

00:03:04.400 --> 00:03:08.160 align:middle line:84%
in the early 20th century,
Alfred Ayer and Ludwig

00:03:08.160 --> 00:03:12.620 align:middle line:84%
Wittgenstein, probably the
most capable, intelligent

00:03:12.620 --> 00:03:15.140 align:middle line:84%
philosophers that
there have ever been,

00:03:15.140 --> 00:03:18.470 align:middle line:84%
said that nothing sensible
can say about God because God

00:03:18.470 --> 00:03:20.330 align:middle line:90%
doesn't have any properties.

00:03:20.330 --> 00:03:24.200 align:middle line:84%
And, in fact, they felt
that any discussion of God

00:03:24.200 --> 00:03:29.330 align:middle line:84%
was nonsense because there
was no sense data available.

00:03:29.330 --> 00:03:32.900 align:middle line:84%
In their later years,
both Wittgenstein and Ayer

00:03:32.900 --> 00:03:34.880 align:middle line:90%
changed their minds somewhat.

00:03:34.880 --> 00:03:37.730 align:middle line:84%
All their lives, they
were believers in data,

00:03:37.730 --> 00:03:40.850 align:middle line:84%
but in the latter part
of Wittgenstein's life,

00:03:40.850 --> 00:03:45.080 align:middle line:84%
for example, in a book--
after the "Tractatus,"

00:03:45.080 --> 00:03:46.700 align:middle line:84%
he wrote a book,
"On Certainty"--

00:03:46.700 --> 00:03:48.690 align:middle line:90%
what do we really know?

00:03:48.690 --> 00:03:52.910 align:middle line:84%
And what he concluded is that
the experience of the mystics

00:03:52.910 --> 00:03:55.280 align:middle line:84%
actually could be
considered data.

00:03:55.280 --> 00:03:57.650 align:middle line:84%
If all the mystics
throughout time

00:03:57.650 --> 00:04:00.230 align:middle line:84%
keep reporting the
same experience,

00:04:00.230 --> 00:04:02.360 align:middle line:84%
maybe we should believe
that they are actually

00:04:02.360 --> 00:04:05.370 align:middle line:84%
having the experience
that they describe.

00:04:05.370 --> 00:04:08.140 align:middle line:84%
In fact, Wittgenstein
said that, if we

00:04:08.140 --> 00:04:12.020 align:middle line:84%
are going to find meaning in
our life, in space and time,

00:04:12.020 --> 00:04:16.110 align:middle line:84%
that meaning will come
outside of space and time.

00:04:16.110 --> 00:04:18.769 align:middle line:84%
So in the end, he decided
that these mystics

00:04:18.769 --> 00:04:20.540 align:middle line:90%
may be onto something.

00:04:20.540 --> 00:04:23.300 align:middle line:84%
>> William James, I
think, had a similar idea.

00:04:23.300 --> 00:04:26.240 align:middle line:84%
James was the founder
of American psychology,

00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:30.260 align:middle line:84%
and he developed a concept
he called radical empiricism,

00:04:30.260 --> 00:04:33.980 align:middle line:84%
in which he said, our
own inner experience

00:04:33.980 --> 00:04:39.500 align:middle line:84%
is the most direct form of
reality that we can know.

00:04:39.500 --> 00:04:43.855 align:middle line:84%
It's primary, whereas sensory
experience is secondary.

00:04:43.855 --> 00:04:44.980 align:middle line:90%
>> I would agree with that.

00:04:44.980 --> 00:04:48.680 align:middle line:84%
We don't want to talk
endlessly about philosophers,

00:04:48.680 --> 00:04:52.640 align:middle line:84%
but CS Peirce, the pragmatist,
English pragmatist,

00:04:52.640 --> 00:04:56.480 align:middle line:84%
who certainly was
nobody's fool, came

00:04:56.480 --> 00:04:58.910 align:middle line:84%
with a paper, "The
Neglected Proof

00:04:58.910 --> 00:05:00.740 align:middle line:90%
for the Existence of God."

00:05:00.740 --> 00:05:05.120 align:middle line:84%
And this neglected proof was the
fact that all of these mystics,

00:05:05.120 --> 00:05:11.790 align:middle line:84%
from Buddha, to Patanjali, to
Jesus, Blake, Emerson, Ramana

00:05:11.790 --> 00:05:14.750 align:middle line:84%
Maharshi, all of these
people who have inspired us

00:05:14.750 --> 00:05:17.060 align:middle line:84%
throughout millennia,
have reported

00:05:17.060 --> 00:05:19.640 align:middle line:90%
very similar experiences.

00:05:19.640 --> 00:05:23.510 align:middle line:84%
And what Peirce
pointed out is that you

00:05:23.510 --> 00:05:25.250 align:middle line:90%
don't have to believe anything.

00:05:25.250 --> 00:05:28.640 align:middle line:84%
What these mystics are saying,
if you quiet your mind,

00:05:28.640 --> 00:05:32.350 align:middle line:84%
this particular kind of
experience is available.

00:05:32.350 --> 00:05:34.790 align:middle line:84%
And it's the experience
that throughout all

00:05:34.790 --> 00:05:38.330 align:middle line:84%
of mystic traditions, say,
is a unit of experience,

00:05:38.330 --> 00:05:41.570 align:middle line:84%
an in-love, one
with God experience,

00:05:41.570 --> 00:05:44.630 align:middle line:84%
and is testable and
independent of belief.

00:05:44.630 --> 00:05:47.930 align:middle line:84%
>> It seems to be independent
of any Sunday school version

00:05:47.930 --> 00:05:50.270 align:middle line:84%
of God, or the
deity, or the Bible.

00:05:50.270 --> 00:05:54.150 align:middle line:84%
>> It gets past the whole
idea of, does God exist?

00:05:54.150 --> 00:05:57.260 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to argue
about God existing.

00:05:57.260 --> 00:06:00.440 align:middle line:84%
Jesus has told us that
God provides a peace that

00:06:00.440 --> 00:06:02.570 align:middle line:84%
passes understanding,
and that peace

00:06:02.570 --> 00:06:06.890 align:middle line:84%
is available as an experience
to anyone who can control

00:06:06.890 --> 00:06:08.090 align:middle line:90%
their own mental chatter.

00:06:08.090 --> 00:06:14.100 align:middle line:84%
>> There's a sense in which God
transcends existence, in that,

00:06:14.100 --> 00:06:15.620 align:middle line:84%
I gather from what
you're saying,

00:06:15.620 --> 00:06:20.090 align:middle line:84%
God is the ground
of all existence.

00:06:20.090 --> 00:06:21.590 align:middle line:84%
>> In the-- I would
agree with that.

00:06:21.590 --> 00:06:24.200 align:middle line:84%
In the perennial philosophy--
the perennial philosophy

00:06:24.200 --> 00:06:27.980 align:middle line:84%
was brought to us throughout
the-- again, throughout all

00:06:27.980 --> 00:06:30.350 align:middle line:84%
the mystical
spiritual traditions,

00:06:30.350 --> 00:06:33.770 align:middle line:84%
and was codified by
Aldous Huxley in his book

00:06:33.770 --> 00:06:34.970 align:middle line:90%
"The Perennial Philosophy."

00:06:34.970 --> 00:06:38.120 align:middle line:84%
What is common to
any spiritual belief?

00:06:38.120 --> 00:06:40.370 align:middle line:84%
And he really had
four elements that

00:06:40.370 --> 00:06:45.410 align:middle line:84%
have become very current with
the advances in modern physics.

00:06:45.410 --> 00:06:48.680 align:middle line:84%
His first element of
the perennial philosophy

00:06:48.680 --> 00:06:50.660 align:middle line:84%
is that we live in
a world that is more

00:06:50.660 --> 00:06:55.220 align:middle line:84%
like a great thought
than a clockwork idea,

00:06:55.220 --> 00:07:01.040 align:middle line:84%
that the universe is a nonlocal,
interconnected universe where

00:07:01.040 --> 00:07:04.730 align:middle line:84%
all parts are connected
to one another.

00:07:04.730 --> 00:07:06.740 align:middle line:84%
The second part of
perennial philosophy

00:07:06.740 --> 00:07:11.320 align:middle line:84%
is the good news is that our
consciousness is also nonlocal,

00:07:11.320 --> 00:07:12.980 align:middle line:84%
so that within
our consciousness,

00:07:12.980 --> 00:07:16.070 align:middle line:84%
we are able to experience
and participate

00:07:16.070 --> 00:07:19.790 align:middle line:84%
in this expanded universe,
that we are not bodies.

00:07:19.790 --> 00:07:21.740 align:middle line:90%
We are awareness.

00:07:21.740 --> 00:07:23.960 align:middle line:84%
We're a center of
awareness located

00:07:23.960 --> 00:07:28.640 align:middle line:84%
in this body for this time,
and this awareness is nonlocal.

00:07:28.640 --> 00:07:32.960 align:middle line:84%
It's able to experience
distant points in space, time,

00:07:32.960 --> 00:07:36.900 align:middle line:84%
because we live in a
nonlocal space and time.

00:07:36.900 --> 00:07:40.460 align:middle line:84%
The third point comes from
our center of awareness

00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:43.100 align:middle line:84%
rather than our
materiality, because we

00:07:43.100 --> 00:07:45.530 align:middle line:90%
know that bodies come and go.

00:07:45.530 --> 00:07:48.530 align:middle line:84%
But the data from
contemporary science--

00:07:48.530 --> 00:07:51.830 align:middle line:84%
Ian Stevenson, for
example, a physician

00:07:51.830 --> 00:07:53.930 align:middle line:84%
at the University
of Virginia, shows

00:07:53.930 --> 00:07:57.020 align:middle line:84%
that there is an aspect
of our personality

00:07:57.020 --> 00:07:59.030 align:middle line:90%
that survives bodily death.

00:07:59.030 --> 00:08:00.590 align:middle line:84%
And you're familiar
with this work,

00:08:00.590 --> 00:08:05.120 align:middle line:84%
where children are born having
memories of a previous life.

00:08:05.120 --> 00:08:06.990 align:middle line:84%
>> You're talking
about reincarnation.

00:08:06.990 --> 00:08:07.790 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:08:07.790 --> 00:08:10.100 align:middle line:84%
There is an aspect
that survives--

00:08:10.100 --> 00:08:12.800 align:middle line:84%
often not much, so
I wouldn't put off

00:08:12.800 --> 00:08:15.470 align:middle line:84%
any plans you want to
accomplish and say,

00:08:15.470 --> 00:08:17.390 align:middle line:90%
I'll do them next lifetime.

00:08:17.390 --> 00:08:19.040 align:middle line:90%
I think that's not prudent.

00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:22.620 align:middle line:84%
But it's evident that this
awareness that we have,

00:08:22.620 --> 00:08:27.500 align:middle line:84%
this nonlocal awareness,
some aspect of that survives.

00:08:27.500 --> 00:08:31.700 align:middle line:84%
And finally, the meaning of
life, the thing that drives us,

00:08:31.700 --> 00:08:34.220 align:middle line:84%
is what you were
asking about initially.

00:08:34.220 --> 00:08:36.380 align:middle line:84%
What drives us and
gives our lives

00:08:36.380 --> 00:08:40.970 align:middle line:84%
meaning is the opportunity
for this unit of experience,

00:08:40.970 --> 00:08:44.810 align:middle line:84%
the opportunity to have
a nonlocal experience,

00:08:44.810 --> 00:08:47.810 align:middle line:84%
a one with God
experience, an opportunity

00:08:47.810 --> 00:08:53.960 align:middle line:84%
to reside in this expanded
love that's available to us.

00:08:53.960 --> 00:08:56.225 align:middle line:84%
And then, what
people discover is

00:08:56.225 --> 00:08:59.420 align:middle line:84%
that the meaning of their
life comes with the desire

00:08:59.420 --> 00:09:01.110 align:middle line:90%
to share that experience.

00:09:01.110 --> 00:09:05.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, Russell, you speak
as one who has found a sense

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:08.150 align:middle line:84%
of peace, a sense of
bliss, and a sense of God.

00:09:08.150 --> 00:09:09.560 align:middle line:90%
And I know it--

00:09:09.560 --> 00:09:12.050 align:middle line:84%
you didn't start
your career this way.

00:09:12.050 --> 00:09:14.090 align:middle line:84%
You weren't even
necessarily looking for this

00:09:14.090 --> 00:09:14.890 align:middle line:90%
when you began.

00:09:14.890 --> 00:09:15.690 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:09:15.690 --> 00:09:16.880 align:middle line:90%
I started as a physicist.

00:09:16.880 --> 00:09:19.400 align:middle line:84%
I was putting-- most
recently, I was putting lasers

00:09:19.400 --> 00:09:21.260 align:middle line:84%
on airplanes at
Lockheed Missiles

00:09:21.260 --> 00:09:25.340 align:middle line:84%
and Space Company in the
heart of the weapons factory.

00:09:25.340 --> 00:09:28.670 align:middle line:84%
And we were looking out into the
future, out into the distance,

00:09:28.670 --> 00:09:31.480 align:middle line:84%
to find wind shear so the
airplane wouldn't crash.

00:09:31.480 --> 00:09:34.760 align:middle line:84%
The very hardware-- this is
remote viewing with lasers.

00:09:34.760 --> 00:09:37.250 align:middle line:84%
>> You've been a physicist
and an engineer all your life.

00:09:37.250 --> 00:09:38.360 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:09:38.360 --> 00:09:42.860 align:middle line:84%
>> So something transformed
you along the way.

00:09:42.860 --> 00:09:45.830 align:middle line:84%
Partially, it was the data,
and, partially, I suppose,

00:09:45.830 --> 00:09:49.130 align:middle line:84%
it was your own personal quest
to make sense of that data.

00:09:49.130 --> 00:09:52.160 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it was a gift of the
CIA that allowed me to spend

00:09:52.160 --> 00:09:55.610 align:middle line:84%
a decade in the dark learning
to do remote viewing,

00:09:55.610 --> 00:09:58.460 align:middle line:84%
helping other people get
in touch with the part

00:09:58.460 --> 00:10:00.440 align:middle line:90%
of themselves that's psychic.

00:10:00.440 --> 00:10:06.170 align:middle line:84%
And it's the discovery that this
nonlocal awareness is available

00:10:06.170 --> 00:10:07.760 align:middle line:90%
that led me to the--

00:10:07.760 --> 00:10:12.260 align:middle line:84%
led me to the pursuit
of getting quiet.

00:10:12.260 --> 00:10:14.120 align:middle line:84%
In Silicon Valley,
for example, we

00:10:14.120 --> 00:10:16.990 align:middle line:84%
find that people are
searching for happiness.

00:10:16.990 --> 00:10:21.320 align:middle line:84%
Everyone is looking to find some
kind of thing that will bring

00:10:21.320 --> 00:10:23.240 align:middle line:90%
them what they're looking for.

00:10:23.240 --> 00:10:25.490 align:middle line:84%
In Silicon Valley,
in general, it's

00:10:25.490 --> 00:10:27.710 align:middle line:90%
something on the material plane.

00:10:27.710 --> 00:10:29.960 align:middle line:84%
If I get a new house
or a new girlfriend

00:10:29.960 --> 00:10:33.230 align:middle line:84%
or a new car, that will all--
that will bring me happiness,

00:10:33.230 --> 00:10:34.230 align:middle line:90%
is the thought.

00:10:34.230 --> 00:10:36.162 align:middle line:84%
Of course, that never
works, as that--

00:10:36.162 --> 00:10:37.370 align:middle line:90%
as a scientist, I could say--

00:10:37.370 --> 00:10:40.100 align:middle line:84%
>> It's as if these things
are a substitute for a deeper

00:10:40.100 --> 00:10:42.140 align:middle line:90%
yearning that people have.

00:10:42.140 --> 00:10:43.030 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:10:43.030 --> 00:10:46.220 align:middle line:84%
As a scientist, I could say
that experiment has been done.

00:10:46.220 --> 00:10:48.980 align:middle line:84%
And what's found
is that happiness

00:10:48.980 --> 00:10:52.730 align:middle line:84%
that a person has in his
life ensues from his life

00:10:52.730 --> 00:10:55.340 align:middle line:84%
experience, and that
happiness is not

00:10:55.340 --> 00:10:58.807 align:middle line:84%
to be found on the
material plane.

00:10:58.807 --> 00:11:00.515 align:middle line:84%
>> Russell, we're
about to take a break--

00:11:00.515 --> 00:11:00.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Fine.

00:11:00.770 --> 00:11:01.570 align:middle line:90%
>> --here.

00:11:01.570 --> 00:11:03.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Could say happiness
is an inside job.

