00:13:17.050 --> 00:13:17.850 align:middle line:90%
But to be an--

00:13:17.850 --> 00:13:19.760 align:middle line:84%
>> But the Buddhists
called them--

00:13:19.760 --> 00:13:21.390 align:middle line:90%
say that there is Anatta.

00:13:21.390 --> 00:13:22.880 align:middle line:90%
There is nothing.

00:13:22.880 --> 00:13:23.960 align:middle line:90%
There is no self.

00:13:23.960 --> 00:13:27.350 align:middle line:84%
It might not-- I think one could
argue that Buddhists are indeed

00:13:27.350 --> 00:13:28.940 align:middle line:90%
atheists.

00:13:28.940 --> 00:13:32.570 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, the Buddhists
are in love with the god--

00:13:32.570 --> 00:13:34.040 align:middle line:90%
one of the Buddhist's deity--

00:13:34.040 --> 00:13:36.800 align:middle line:84%
I think there are different
kinds of Buddhism, as you know.

00:13:36.800 --> 00:13:38.720 align:middle line:84%
The Buddhists are
in love with the god

00:13:38.720 --> 00:13:40.810 align:middle line:90%
of compassion, Avalokitesvara--

00:13:40.810 --> 00:13:41.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes.

00:13:41.610 --> 00:13:47.150 align:middle line:84%
>> --the god who will come down
to you and be in your locus

00:13:47.150 --> 00:13:48.800 align:middle line:90%
and bring you compassion.

00:13:48.800 --> 00:13:53.570 align:middle line:84%
So to say that it's free of
deities is an overstatement.

00:13:53.570 --> 00:13:57.740 align:middle line:84%
That is, people can pray to
this favorite compassionate god,

00:13:57.740 --> 00:13:59.120 align:middle line:90%
even if you're a Buddhist.

00:13:59.120 --> 00:14:02.090 align:middle line:84%
>> But the Buddhists would
also say, I think, you know,

00:14:02.090 --> 00:14:03.230 align:middle line:90%
that they don't exist--

00:14:03.230 --> 00:14:07.550 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] either that they're--
that there is no self.

00:14:07.550 --> 00:14:09.020 align:middle line:90%
There's, like, an energy.

00:14:09.020 --> 00:14:10.610 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, coming
back to reality--

00:14:10.610 --> 00:14:11.620 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:14:11.620 --> 00:14:16.160 align:middle line:84%
>> --what we observe is that
we have a center awareness,

00:14:16.160 --> 00:14:17.600 align:middle line:90%
is we are aware.

00:14:17.600 --> 00:14:19.460 align:middle line:90%
We're not physical bodies.

00:14:19.460 --> 00:14:23.510 align:middle line:84%
We're a center of awareness
residing in a physical body.

00:14:23.510 --> 00:14:27.320 align:middle line:84%
Thinking that your physical body
is a source of great suffering,

00:14:27.320 --> 00:14:31.850 align:middle line:84%
especially in America, where
all the advertising we see

00:14:31.850 --> 00:14:35.540 align:middle line:84%
is concerning physical
bodies and appearances

00:14:35.540 --> 00:14:41.000 align:middle line:84%
and the hopelessness of
looking like Barbie, which

00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:43.340 align:middle line:90%
is outside physical reality--

00:14:43.340 --> 00:14:46.070 align:middle line:84%
the idea that the shape
of your physical body

00:14:46.070 --> 00:14:49.970 align:middle line:84%
determines who you are,
whereas what we know

00:14:49.970 --> 00:14:54.080 align:middle line:84%
is that who you are is a
center of awareness temporarily

00:14:54.080 --> 00:14:55.850 align:middle line:90%
residing in this body.

00:14:55.850 --> 00:14:57.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:14:57.260 --> 00:14:59.100 align:middle line:84%
Well, there are
many paradoxes here,

00:14:59.100 --> 00:15:01.800 align:middle line:84%
when we get into the
nature of the self,

00:15:01.800 --> 00:15:06.000 align:middle line:90%
the nature of the deity.

00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:09.840 align:middle line:84%
>> The expanded awareness we
were talking about is a clue

00:15:09.840 --> 00:15:13.710 align:middle line:84%
that there is more to us than
the skin and bones and the meat

00:15:13.710 --> 00:15:14.940 align:middle line:90%
and potatoes.

00:15:14.940 --> 00:15:18.300 align:middle line:84%
>> By which you're referring
to our discussion in part 1,

00:15:18.300 --> 00:15:21.730 align:middle line:84%
of extrasensory perception and
your decades of work in that

00:15:21.730 --> 00:15:22.530 align:middle line:90%
field.

00:15:22.530 --> 00:15:25.500 align:middle line:84%
>> We were talking
about remote viewing,

00:15:25.500 --> 00:15:28.950 align:middle line:84%
or the opportunity that we
have to look into the distance

00:15:28.950 --> 00:15:33.150 align:middle line:84%
or look into the future, is a
clue that there's more to us

00:15:33.150 --> 00:15:37.140 align:middle line:84%
than the physicality that
you see sitting in a chair.

00:15:37.140 --> 00:15:39.960 align:middle line:84%
And the Hindu teacher
Patanjali, who

00:15:39.960 --> 00:15:44.100 align:middle line:84%
was 300 years before
Christ, told his students

00:15:44.100 --> 00:15:47.780 align:middle line:84%
and wrote in his books
the "Sutras of Patanjali,"

00:15:47.780 --> 00:15:49.320 align:middle line:90%
which are still available--

00:15:49.320 --> 00:15:50.310 align:middle line:90%
>> The Yoga Sutras.

00:15:50.310 --> 00:15:52.230 align:middle line:84%
>> --that, as you
quiet your mind,

00:15:52.230 --> 00:15:55.020 align:middle line:84%
you will have these
interesting experiences.

00:15:55.020 --> 00:15:57.810 align:middle line:84%
You will be able to
look into the distance,

00:15:57.810 --> 00:16:01.140 align:middle line:84%
look into future
time, heal the sick,

00:16:01.140 --> 00:16:06.040 align:middle line:84%
diagnose illnesses as part
of expanding your awareness.

00:16:06.040 --> 00:16:09.420 align:middle line:84%
And he then went on
to say, now, don't

00:16:09.420 --> 00:16:11.190 align:middle line:90%
get attached to these things.

00:16:11.190 --> 00:16:13.680 align:middle line:90%
This is just more phenomena.

00:16:13.680 --> 00:16:17.220 align:middle line:84%
But these phenomena show
that you are progressing

00:16:17.220 --> 00:16:19.270 align:middle line:90%
on a spiritual path.

00:16:19.270 --> 00:16:20.910 align:middle line:84%
Now, the spiritual
path that you want

00:16:20.910 --> 00:16:24.150 align:middle line:84%
to be on leads to
transcendence, leads

00:16:24.150 --> 00:16:27.270 align:middle line:84%
to a unity-consciousness
experience.

00:16:27.270 --> 00:16:30.750 align:middle line:84%
Patanjali was a Hindu,
so he would probably

00:16:30.750 --> 00:16:35.160 align:middle line:84%
be happy saying that it was
a one with God experience.

00:16:35.160 --> 00:16:37.770 align:middle line:84%
More contemporary,
Jesus might say

00:16:37.770 --> 00:16:41.250 align:middle line:84%
that it's an in-love
experience, and Jesus taught us

00:16:41.250 --> 00:16:43.020 align:middle line:90%
that God is love.

00:16:43.020 --> 00:16:47.130 align:middle line:84%
Contemporary teachers
like Ramana Maharshi,

00:16:47.130 --> 00:16:50.370 align:middle line:84%
who talked about
self-inquiry, would

00:16:50.370 --> 00:16:55.290 align:middle line:84%
say that it's an opportunity
to experience who you are

00:16:55.290 --> 00:16:59.430 align:middle line:84%
and surrender your story,
as giving up your story

00:16:59.430 --> 00:17:04.440 align:middle line:84%
is an opportunity to participate
in this expanded awareness,

00:17:04.440 --> 00:17:08.730 align:middle line:84%
to give up the
drive for happiness

00:17:08.730 --> 00:17:11.910 align:middle line:84%
on the material plane, but
rather to find happiness

00:17:11.910 --> 00:17:12.900 align:middle line:90%
inside.

00:17:12.900 --> 00:17:16.560 align:middle line:84%
So all of these mystics are
leading in the same direction.

00:17:16.560 --> 00:17:18.750 align:middle line:84%
And what they all
have in common is

00:17:18.750 --> 00:17:21.390 align:middle line:84%
that they don't want
you to believe a thing.

00:17:21.390 --> 00:17:23.310 align:middle line:90%
They say, try this.

00:17:23.310 --> 00:17:25.740 align:middle line:90%
This experience is available.

00:17:25.740 --> 00:17:29.820 align:middle line:84%
And you could say that God
is a testable hypothesis

00:17:29.820 --> 00:17:33.010 align:middle line:84%
in the spirit of all the
mystics, where they agree.

00:17:33.010 --> 00:17:34.560 align:middle line:84%
>> So you're
suggesting to people,

00:17:34.560 --> 00:17:37.380 align:middle line:84%
who may not know what
you're talking about,

00:17:37.380 --> 00:17:40.320 align:middle line:84%
that they can take some
simple steps to, well,

00:17:40.320 --> 00:17:42.170 align:middle line:90%
discover for themselves.

00:17:42.170 --> 00:17:43.940 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, the simple
steps, of course,

00:17:43.940 --> 00:17:48.150 align:middle line:84%
involve first of all observing
that happiness is not going

00:17:48.150 --> 00:17:49.850 align:middle line:84%
to be found on the
material plane.

00:17:49.850 --> 00:17:51.225 align:middle line:84%
Now, that's a big
disappointment.

00:17:51.225 --> 00:17:54.030 align:middle line:84%
>> And you pointed out, even
meaning is not to be found

00:17:54.030 --> 00:17:55.110 align:middle line:90%
in the material plane.

00:17:55.110 --> 00:17:59.460 align:middle line:84%
>> That's right, because we give
the meaning for our experiences

00:17:59.460 --> 00:18:00.660 align:middle line:90%
from our own choice.

00:18:00.660 --> 00:18:03.210 align:middle line:84%
That is, what we
experience intrinsically

00:18:03.210 --> 00:18:06.360 align:middle line:84%
doesn't have any meaning
beyond what we give it.

00:18:06.360 --> 00:18:09.570 align:middle line:84%
But once we learn
to quiet our mind

00:18:09.570 --> 00:18:14.520 align:middle line:84%
and to reside in this peaceful
place with a quiet mind,

00:18:14.520 --> 00:18:18.510 align:middle line:84%
then we have an opportunity
for these experiences.

00:18:18.510 --> 00:18:22.080 align:middle line:84%
What we discover is
that love is available.

00:18:22.080 --> 00:18:25.440 align:middle line:84%
And in the interactions we
have with different people,

00:18:25.440 --> 00:18:27.600 align:middle line:84%
the interaction you
have from a person

00:18:27.600 --> 00:18:31.500 align:middle line:84%
is either an expression of
love or a call for love.

00:18:31.500 --> 00:18:36.630 align:middle line:84%
Even the disagreeable
person one is working for

00:18:36.630 --> 00:18:40.020 align:middle line:84%
or the tired person at
the counter is not--

00:18:40.020 --> 00:18:41.460 align:middle line:90%
doesn't hate you.

00:18:41.460 --> 00:18:43.050 align:middle line:90%
He's just calling for love.

00:18:43.050 --> 00:18:45.540 align:middle line:90%
He's having a desperate day.

00:18:45.540 --> 00:18:48.750 align:middle line:84%
And you can greet
him with the idea

00:18:48.750 --> 00:18:53.220 align:middle line:84%
that the nonlocal
awareness in you

00:18:53.220 --> 00:18:56.640 align:middle line:84%
recognizes the nonlocal
awareness in him,

00:18:56.640 --> 00:18:59.700 align:middle line:84%
and that you are, in fact,
one, that you're connected.

00:18:59.700 --> 00:19:02.580 align:middle line:84%
So the metaphysics
that we are all one

00:19:02.580 --> 00:19:06.000 align:middle line:84%
is today finding
a great coherence

00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:07.890 align:middle line:84%
with modern physics
that says that we

00:19:07.890 --> 00:19:10.410 align:middle line:84%
are, in fact,
nonlocal creatures,

00:19:10.410 --> 00:19:14.340 align:middle line:84%
profoundly interacting with one
another across space and time.

00:19:14.340 --> 00:19:18.420 align:middle line:84%
>> And you earlier referred
to the idea of intentionality,

00:19:18.420 --> 00:19:21.510 align:middle line:84%
as well as awareness, that when
we get in touch with what you

00:19:21.510 --> 00:19:29.160 align:middle line:84%
refer to as our nonlocal self,
we have the facility to express

00:19:29.160 --> 00:19:32.895 align:middle line:84%
a kind of joyful, exuberant,
loving, healing energy,

00:19:32.895 --> 00:19:35.190 align:middle line:90%
and as part of our experience.

00:19:35.190 --> 00:19:38.620 align:middle line:84%
>> The nonlocality is the most
important message I could leave

00:19:38.620 --> 00:19:39.420 align:middle line:90%
with you.

00:19:39.420 --> 00:19:41.280 align:middle line:84%
That is, in modern
physics, we now

00:19:41.280 --> 00:19:44.460 align:middle line:84%
know that we live in
a nonlocal universe.

00:19:44.460 --> 00:19:47.340 align:middle line:84%
It's not to say that
extrasensory perception is

00:19:47.340 --> 00:19:51.560 align:middle line:84%
explained by the fact that
distant photons are connected.

00:19:51.560 --> 00:19:54.450 align:middle line:84%
In the Einstein-Podolsky-Rosen
experiment,

00:19:54.450 --> 00:19:58.050 align:middle line:84%
we observe that these photons
traveling away from each other

00:19:58.050 --> 00:19:59.400 align:middle line:90%
are connected.

00:19:59.400 --> 00:20:01.170 align:middle line:84%
And what that
shows us is that we

00:20:01.170 --> 00:20:04.590 align:middle line:84%
live in a profoundly
interconnected world, quite

00:20:04.590 --> 00:20:09.030 align:middle line:84%
compatible with the various
kinds of psychic things we see.

00:20:09.030 --> 00:20:12.810 align:middle line:84%
The outflow of intention that
we see in spiritual healing

00:20:12.810 --> 00:20:17.670 align:middle line:84%
is another manifestation of
these nonlocal connections.

00:20:17.670 --> 00:20:20.460 align:middle line:84%
And more and more,
we see data published

00:20:20.460 --> 00:20:25.080 align:middle line:84%
in prestigious medical journals
that healers across the country

00:20:25.080 --> 00:20:29.580 align:middle line:84%
can pray for cardiac
patients or AIDS patients,

00:20:29.580 --> 00:20:31.830 align:middle line:90%
and in the experiments--

00:20:31.830 --> 00:20:34.620 align:middle line:84%
recently, my daughter,
Elizabeth Targ,

00:20:34.620 --> 00:20:38.370 align:middle line:84%
did experiments at California
Pacific Medical Center.

00:20:38.370 --> 00:20:43.080 align:middle line:84%
And with 60 very sick
men, the half, the 30 men,

00:20:43.080 --> 00:20:45.840 align:middle line:84%
who were the
recipients of prayers

00:20:45.840 --> 00:20:47.430 align:middle line:90%
had much better outcomes.

00:20:47.430 --> 00:20:49.770 align:middle line:84%
They had fewer
opportunistic illnesses,

00:20:49.770 --> 00:20:52.710 align:middle line:84%
fewer trips to the
hospital, fewer

00:20:52.710 --> 00:20:56.430 align:middle line:84%
days in the hospital, better
self-reports of how they feel.

00:20:56.430 --> 00:20:58.335 align:middle line:84%
And these were
double-blind studies,

00:20:58.335 --> 00:21:02.070 align:middle line:84%
that no one in the hospital,
including the patients,

00:21:02.070 --> 00:21:04.740 align:middle line:84%
knew who was
receiving the prayers.

00:21:04.740 --> 00:21:06.810 align:middle line:84%
But at the end, where
there was a review

00:21:06.810 --> 00:21:11.550 align:middle line:84%
of the charts, the people
for whom the distant prayers,

00:21:11.550 --> 00:21:13.710 align:middle line:84%
those distant people
were able to have

00:21:13.710 --> 00:21:16.560 align:middle line:84%
an effect on the
physical well-being

00:21:16.560 --> 00:21:18.360 align:middle line:90%
of the people in the hospital.

00:21:18.360 --> 00:21:21.450 align:middle line:84%
And this was published in the
"Western Medical Journal,"

00:21:21.450 --> 00:21:24.030 align:middle line:84%
and similar studies
with cardiac patients

00:21:24.030 --> 00:21:27.330 align:middle line:84%
have been published in "Annals
of Medicine" and "Southern

00:21:27.330 --> 00:21:31.990 align:middle line:84%
Medical Journal," involving many
hundreds of cardiac patients.

00:21:31.990 --> 00:21:35.760 align:middle line:84%
So it's absolutely
evident that the effects

00:21:35.760 --> 00:21:39.190 align:middle line:84%
of these distant people
are having an effect.

00:21:39.190 --> 00:21:42.210 align:middle line:84%
So the message is that, even
if you don't believe in prayer,

00:21:42.210 --> 00:21:44.490 align:middle line:84%
and somebody offers
to pray for you,

00:21:44.490 --> 00:21:45.780 align:middle line:90%
you should accept the prayers.

00:21:45.780 --> 00:21:48.300 align:middle line:84%
It seems to work, even if
you don't believe in it.

00:21:48.300 --> 00:21:50.070 align:middle line:84%
>> And your daughter,
Elizabeth Targ,

00:21:50.070 --> 00:21:53.310 align:middle line:84%
one of the country's leading
researchers in this area,

00:21:53.310 --> 00:21:55.850 align:middle line:84%
is scheduled to be a
guest on this program.

00:21:55.850 --> 00:21:57.600 align:middle line:84%
>> That should be a
